      "scene_defaults": {
        "title": "A Working Theory of Print",
        "narration": "The studios betting on print are not nostalgists. They have read the same charts as everyone else and reached a contrary conclusion: that attention, not paper, is the scarce resource worth fighting for. A magazine demands a kind of focus the feed cannot, and — when the columns settle and the rules align — it repays the effort. The grid becomes a quiet promise that nothing here is accidental, and that the reader's time has been respected. That promise, more than any typeface, is what keeps the format alive.",
